==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumvent
<hw>Cir`cum*vent"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Circumvented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Circumventing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumventis</ets>, p. p. of <ets>circumvenire</ets>, to come
around, encompass, deceive; <ets>circum</ets> + <ets>venire</ets> to
come, akin to E. <ets>come.</ets>]</ety> <def>To gain advantage over by
arts, stratagem, or deception; to deceive; to delude; to get
around.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>circumvented</qex> whom I could not gain.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumvention</ent>⟦br⟧
